          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIyF3-ALuGMEEW91cCQ-muIDvKfZvPuRSH_A1I4TmtBbQsPow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "Had a terrible customer service experience. Called the office Monday Dec15th and spoke with someone about my son who just got home from college who needs a wisdom tooth extracted. I told them he is leaving Jan 13th so needs to be seen before then. She said that is fine and told me the price for the initial visit and the starting range if we don\u2019t have insurance. We do so I told her I would call the insurance to confirm the coverage and call her back. I called back on Wednesday Dec17th and she was in a meeting so I asked for a call back. They assured me that she would call back after the meeting. Never received a call back. I called back on Thursday Dec 18th. Once again told her the situation and gave her all the insurance info. She said she would call back to set the appointment. She called back a few hours later to ask for the zip code and said she would call again. Never did. I called back again the morning of Friday Dec 19th. The woman I spoke that morning said there are no appointments before the second week of January and that the other woman didn\u2019t know that. So I wasted a week thinking my son could be seen because employees don\u2019t know there are no appointments? How is that possible? Before gathering social security numbers shouldn\u2019t they be checking availability on an easy to access scheduling system? Very disorganized.",
